Here's my plan for adding the `mistral-instruct-v3` handler. **Two surgical edits to `common/chat.cpp` only** — no other files touched.

---

### Change 1 — New handler function
**Insert after line 1517** (the closing `}` of `gigachat_v3`), before the `namespace workaround` block:

```cpp
// Mistral Instruct v0.3 - classic [INST]/[/INST] wrapping, no tool-call syntax
static common_chat_params common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(
        const common_chat_template & /*tmpl*/,
        const autoparser::generation_params & inputs) {
    common_chat_params data;

    std::string prompt;
    std::string pending_system;
    bool is_first = true;

    for (const auto & msg : inputs.messages) {
        const auto role    = msg.value("role", "");
        const auto content = msg.value("content", "");

        if (role == "system") {
            pending_system = content;
        } else if (role == "user") {
            if (is_first) { prompt += "<s>"; is_first = false; }
            prompt += "[INST] ";
            if (!pending_system.empty()) {
                prompt += pending_system + "\n";
                pending_system.clear();
            }
            prompt += content + " [/INST]";
        } else if (role == "assistant") {
            prompt += " " + content + "</s>";
        }
    }

    data.prompt = prompt;
    data.format = COMMON_CHAT_FORMAT_CONTENT_ONLY;
    return data;
}
```

This produces exactly the required format:
- With system: `<s>[INST] {system}\n{user1} [/INST] {assistant1}</s>[INST] {user2} [/INST]`
- Without system: `<s>[INST] {user1} [/INST] {assistant1}</s>[INST] {user2} [/INST]`

### Change 2 — Detection block
**Insert before `return std::nullopt;` at line 1690** (last entry in `common_chat_try_specialized_template`):

```cpp
    // Mistral Instruct v3 - [INST]/[/INST] without [SYSTEM_PROMPT]
    if (src.find("[INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[/INST]") != std::string::npos &&
        src.find("[SYSTEM_PROMPT]") == std::string::npos) {
        LOG_DBG("Using specialized template: Mistral Instruct v3\n");
        return common_chat_params_init_mistral_instruct_v3(tmpl, params);
    }
```

**Key safety property:** The existing Ministral 3 handler requires `[SYSTEM_PROMPT]` to be *present* — the new check requires it to be *absent* — so they are mutually exclusive and ordering doesn't matter. Placing this last ensures all other more-specific handlers remain unaffected.
